THE CERTIFICATED PRIVATE WAS LANDING IN A TAIL WHEEL AIRPLANE AND 
ENCOUNTERED CROSS WIND CONDITIONS FROM THE RIGHT. DURING THE LANDING 
ROLL, THE PILOT DID NOT MAINTAIN DIRECTIONAL CONTROL AND THE AIRPLANE 
VEERED TO THE RIGHT, OFF THE RUNWAY AND BEGAN TO GROUND LOOP. THE 
PILOT APPLIED HARD BRAKING AND THE AIRPLANE NOSED OVER. 
A FAILURE OF THE PILOT TO ADEQUATELY COMPENSATE FOR CROSS WIND 
CONDITIONS AND A FAILURE TO MAINTAIN DIRECTIONAL CONTROL OF THE 
AIRPLANE. 
